      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Week 3 of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Data.Punk."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "You enter a ZIP code. The app quietly contacts three federal agencies — the Census Bureau, the EPA, and FEMA — and pulls the data they've been sitting on about your neighborhood: median income, poverty rate, the age of your housing stock, every EPA-regulated facility nearby, how many have active violations, and every disaster declaration your county has absorbed in the last five years. Then Claude reads all three datasets together and writes a classified-style intelligence dossier — cross-referencing patterns across agencies that no single agency ever connected for you. The government collected all of this. They just never put it together."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Worth noting alongside this: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com/p/preparing-for-summer-into-ai-week3",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Eric's Space Weather Explorer"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " Eric went outward — pulling NASA MMS4 magnetic field data and rendering it in Three.js particles. FOIA Ghost went inward: the same data-punk ethos applied to the ground beneath your feet, using EPA, Census, and FEMA data to surface what the federal government knows about your specific neighborhood"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Three live federal APIs, fetched in parallel."
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " The /api/fetch endpoint calls Census ACS 2022 (income, poverty, housing age, internet access), EPA ECHO (regulated facilities in the ZIP, significant non-compliance flags), and FEMA disaster declarations — all in a single Promise.allSettled call. Each dataset streams into its own terminal panel with a typewriter animation as it arrives."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Extended thinking, streamed live."
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " The /api/analyze endpoint calls Claude Sonnet with thinking: { type: 'enabled', budget_tokens: 5000 } and betas: ['interleaved-thinking-2025-05-14']. Claude's reasoning process — the cross-dataset analysis happening before the dossier is written — streams to a collapsible REASONING section in real time. You watch Claude think before it writes."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Cross-dataset synthesis as the product."
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " Claude is given all three datasets simultaneously and instructed to find connections none of the agencies made individually — like when above-average poverty, pre-1960 housing, and nearby EPA violations combine into a lead-paint-plus-exposure pattern that no single dataset shows. The dossier streams section by section: Economic Profile, Environmental Exposure, Disaster Vulnerability, and the Ghost Analysis classified findings."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Enter any US ZIP code and hit TRANSMIT"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Watch three terminal panels fill with real Census, EPA, and FEMA data for your area"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The GHOST ANALYSIS section opens — you can expand REASONING STREAM to watch Claude think through the cross-dataset connections in real time"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Read the dossier: Economic Profile, Environmental Exposure, Disaster Vulnerability, and the classified Ghost Analysis findings"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A color-coded risk badge appears at the end: NOMINAL, ELEVATED, HIGH, or CRITICAL"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
